description:
icmpv6.py:230 - handle_icmpv6() parses and responds to Echo Requests without calling verify_checksum(). RFC 4443 Section 2.4 requires: 'Every ICMPv6 message MUST have its checksum field verified before being processed.'

Failure scenario: An attacker or network corruption produces an ICMPv6 Echo Request with an invalid checksum. The handler processes it anyway, generating a reply to a malformed/spoofed packet.

Fix: Add checksum verification at the start of handle_icmpv6:
  if not Icmpv6Message.verify_checksum(packet.header.src_addr, packet.header.dst_addr, packet.payload):
      return None  # or raise Icmpv6Error('checksum failed')
